column2: Browser extension for rendering an isometric pixel art version of your GitHub contribution graph.

column5:
Merge pull request #106 from brandon1024/tab-switch-fix

Re-render Chart When Switching Date Ranges

Re-render Chart When Switching Tabs

When selecting a new date range, re-render the chart for the new commit
history data. It appears as though it was once working, but changes on
the GitHub side required changes to the extension to handle it.

The event handler for 'pjax:success' was no longer invoked, and would
not re-render the chart, so it could be safely removed.
Use zip files for firefox instead of xpi

Merge pull request #44 from deltaidea/consolidate-coffee

Consolidate code base for all extensions

Move `iso.coffee` to `src/`, compile it to all extensions using `src/build.sh`

Common codebase is a good thing, right?

Add universal `persistSetting` method for both `chrome.storage` and `localStorage`

This allows to have a common codebase for the extension as `iso.coffee` is otherwise
identical for all three browsers.

Load settings before rendering to avoid chart flickering on page load

When normal chart view is selected, the isometric view is rendered anyway. This allows to
instantly switch to it later, but if we load settings asynchonously, the chart flickers
on page load: the isometric view is switched on by default, and then turned off once
the settings are loaded.

This commit fixes that problem by moving settings loading to a separate method and
calling `renderIsometricChart` and `initUI` in its callback.
